Executive Profile
Gregory T. Barmore  Independent Director, A. Schulman, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 2 different industries.See Board Relationships75$160,182
Background

		Mr. Gregory T. Barmore, also known as Greg, served as the Chief Executive Officer at GE Capital Mortgage Corp. from 1986 to 1997. Mr. Barmore was responsible for overseeing the strategic development of GECMC's residential real estate-affiliated financial business, including mortgage insurance, mortgage services and mortgage funding. Prior to joining GECMC in 1986, he served as the Chief Financial Officer of Employers Reinsurance Corp. (ERC), also a subsidiary of GE Capital. ... Prior to his ERC appointment in 1984, he held a number of financial and general management positions within GE, including General Manager of the International Watt-hour Meter Business and Chief Financial Officer of the Electrical Distribution Equipment Business. During his mortgage career, he served as President of Mortgage Insurance Companies of America and the Consumer Mortgage Coalition and was a member of the Mortgage Bankers of America Board of Governors. He served as the Chairman of the Board of ICO - Schulman, LLC. Mr. Barmore served as the Chairman at GE Capital Mortgage Corp. He served as the Chairman since October 2005 and Director since June 2004 of ICO Polymers. He serves as a Director of ICO - Schulman, LLC. He serves as a Director of Harbor Technologies, LLC. He serves as Lead Independent Director of Novastar Financial Inc. He has been a Director of Novastar Financial Inc. since 1996. He has been Independent Director of A. Schulman, Inc. since May 2010. He serves on the boards of Orion Ropeworks Inc., and Thos. Moser Cabinetmakers. He served as a Director of Novation Companies, Inc., since 1996 and served as its Lead Independent Director. In addition, he serves as a Trustee of Bennett College, The Maine Maritime Museum and Maine Island Trail Association. He serves as the President of Holbrooks Community Foundation. Mr. Barmore is a Graduate of Tufts University with a Bachelor of Science degree in Economics.Read Full Background




